<p>The <code>max_len</code> function truncates text to a maximum length with ellipsis.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | max_len(15){close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{echo $sampleText | max_len(15)}</b></p>

<h2>Short Text</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'Hi' | max_len(10){close}</pre>
<p>Short: <b>{echo 'Hi' | max_len(10)}</b></p>

<h2>Long Text</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'This is a very long text that should be truncated' | max_len(20){close}</pre>
<p>Truncated: <b>{echo 'This is a very long text that should be truncated' | max_len(20)}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | trim | max_len(12){close}</pre>
<p>Clean truncate: <b>{echo $sampleText | trim | max_len(12)}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo $email | max_len(15) | html{close}</pre>
<p>Safe display: <b>{echo $email | max_len(15) | html}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Adds ellipsis (...) when text exceeds the limit. The count includes the ellipsis.</p>
